Meanwhile in 1522 he was chosen as Preacher to the church at Miltenberg ; but being accused of heresy by Cochlaeus. in 1524 he was driven back to Wittenberg. Amid varying fortunes he married, and spent some years at Eisenach at work upon a Polyglot Bible. From 1534—47 he was Professor 01· Theology at Marburg, until doctrinal differences forced him to leave. After a settlement at Lubeck he was at Rostock University from 1551 till 1560, when Duke Albert of Prussia set him over the bpric. of Pomerania.
